Keep the crosshair/reticle visible when the HUD is hidden via "Hide UI".

Unlike the floating actor-name tooltips (a sibling widget, handled in
companion-keep-actor-names-on-hideui.patch), the crosshair is a CHILD of the
HUD's main widget (openmw_hud.layout: "Crosshair" inside "_Main"). The Hide UI
toggle hides the whole HUD via mHud->setVisible(mHudEnabled && !loading), and
MyGUI's inherited-visibility propagation hides every child with it — including
the crosshair. There is no separate mHudEnabled gate on the crosshair to relax.

The crosshair's real visibility is already driven every frame by
setCrosshairVisible(), called from WindowManager::showCrosshair():
  - camera.cpp: showCrosshair(!isGuiMode() && mShowCrosshair) every frame
    (hidden in menus/loading and in third person),
  - inputmanagerimp.cpp: showCrosshair(false) on entering GUI mode,
  - gated additionally by Settings::hud().mCrosshair.

So we detach the crosshair from the HUD main widget in the HUD constructor,
making it an independent root widget on the same "HUD" layer. Hiding mHud no
longer affects it, while all of its own hide conditions remain intact.
detachFromWidget() resets the widget's absolute position to its local coord
(0,0 in the layout), so we recenter it on the viewport and make it
click-through (a reticle must never steal the centre tap from the world).

--- a/apps/openmw/mwgui/hud.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwgui/hud.cpp
@@ -92,5 +92,21 @@
         getWidget(mWeaponSpellBox, "WeaponSpellName");

         getWidget(mCrosshair, "Crosshair");
+
+        // COMPANION: detach the crosshair from the HUD's main widget so it is not
+        // hidden when the HUD is toggled off via "Hide UI" — mHud->setVisible(false)
+        // would otherwise hide it through MyGUI's inherited visibility. Its own
+        // visibility is still fully managed every frame by setCrosshairVisible()
+        // (driven from the camera: hidden in GUI mode / third person / when the
+        // crosshair setting is off). detachFromWidget() resets the widget to its
+        // local coord (0,0), so recenter it on the viewport and make it click-through.
+        mCrosshair->detachFromWidget("HUD");
+        mCrosshair->setNeedMouseFocus(false);
+        {
+            const MyGUI::IntSize& crossView = MyGUI::RenderManager::getInstance().getViewSize();
+            const MyGUI::IntSize crossSize = mCrosshair->getSize();
+            mCrosshair->setCoord((crossView.width - crossSize.width) / 2,
+                (crossView.height - crossSize.height) / 2, crossSize.width, crossSize.height);
+        }

         LocalMapBase::init(mMinimap, mCompass);
